&ldquo;This is the most important book ever written about time management. Oliver Burkeman offers a searing indictment of productivity hacking and profound insights on how to make the best use of our scarcest, most precious resource. His writing will challenge you to rethink many of your beliefs about getting things done-and you&rsquo;ll be wiser because of it.&rdquo;&nbsp;
-Adam Grant, #1&nbsp; New York Times&nbsp; bestselling author of&nbsp; Think Again &nbsp;and host of&nbsp; WorkLife 
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Time is our biggest worry: there is too little of it. The award-winning, renowned Guardian columnist Oliver Burkeman offers a lively, entertaining philosophical guide to time and time management, setting aside superficial efficiency solutions in favour of reckoning with and finding joy in the finitude of human life. 
The average human lifespan is absurdly, insultingly brief. Assuming you live to be...
